        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-02-28 19:53:53.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nJorge, yes, the assertTrue's are trivial and technically aren't needed. However, sonar shouldn't complain because from its perspective the tests could potentially fail if an exception is thrown by another class's logic somewhere else in the call stack. You could probably trigger an exception based off of the properties you provide in the *.properties file you pass to the test.",
